{{Quote|They call me terrorist. Radical. Zealot. Because I obey the ancient laws of my people, the [[Kree]], and punish those who do not. Because I do not forgive [[Xandarians|your people]] for taking the life of my father and his father and his father before him. A thousand years of [[Kree-Nova War|war]] between us will not be forgotten!|Ronan|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
'''Ronan''' was a radical [[Kree]] warlord and a former '''[[Accusers|Accuser]]''' of the [[Kree Empire]]. A participant in the [[Kree-Skrull War]], Ronan worked with [[Yon-Rogg]] and the [[Starforce]] after the [[Ambush in Torfa]] to wipe out the last of the [[Skrull]] refugees. Ronan and the Accusers were then called to drop warheads on [[Earth]] to wipe out the remaining Skrull opposition there, but were repelled when [[Captain Marvel]] came to Earth's defense. The Accusers retreated, with Ronan promising retribution.

Further disgusted by an armistice made between the [[Kree Empire|Kree]] and [[Nova Empire]]s to end the [[Kree-Nova War]], Ronan initiated a new campaign to eradicate the [[Xandarians]] by forging an alliance with [[Thanos]], offering the [[Orb]] in exchange for the destruction of [[Xandar]]. After a long [[Quest for the Orb|search]], Ronan acquired the Orb, but after realizing it had housed the [[Power Stone]], he instead betrayed Thanos and chose to take the Orb's power for himself. Using his new-found power, he and his forces [[Battle of Xandar|attacked]] Xandar, only to be defeated and killed by the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]].

==Biography==
===Early Life===
====Losing Relatives====
Ronan was born [[Before 20th Century|centuries ago]] on the planet [[Hala]], the ancestral homeworld of the [[Kree]] into an Imperial family which generations had fought and died in the thousand year [[Kree-Nova War]] between the Kree and [[Xandarians]].{{Ref|MSCE}} During the war, Ronan lost his father, his grandfather and his great-grandfather.{{Ref|GotG}} This led him to develop a strong feeling of hate and repulsion for [[Xandar]] and its culture.{{Ref|MSVD}}

===[[Kree-Skrull War]]===
====Hunting Down the Skrulls====
[[File:Captain Marvel VFX 12.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan berates [[Starforce]]'s [[Ambush in Torfa|failure]]]]
{{Quote|We'll be back for the weapon."<br>"The [[Tesseract|core]]?"<br>"The [[Captain Marvel|woman]].|Ronan and [[Accuser]]|Captain Marvel (film)}}
By the [[Kree-Skrull War]], Ronan had joined the [[Accusers]], becoming the lead Accuser in charge of the [[Accuser Warship]]s fleet.{{Ref|CMAC}} In [[1995]], using several warships, Ronan and his Accusers dropped warheads onto [[Torfa]] to [[Ambush in Torfa|eliminate]] the [[Skrulls]] and clear the way for the [[Starforce]] so they could rescue [[Soh-Larr]]. However, it turned out that the Skrulls had ambushed the Starforce in an attempt to capture [[Vers]]. Following her abduction, Ronan contacted [[Yon-Rogg]] and blamed the Starforce for the failure of the mission.
[[File:Yon-Rogg calls Ronan.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan is ordered to come above [[Earth]]]]
Yon-Rogg later called Ronan after Vers had discovered that the [[Kree]], were the aggressors in the Kree-Skrull War the whole time and not the Skrulls. Yon-Rogg ordered Ronan and the Accusers to come above [[Earth]] and drop [[Kree Ballistic Missiles]] in order to eliminate [[Talos]] and the remaining Skrulls under the orders of the [[Supreme Intelligence]]. Ronan arrived in the midst of the [[Battle at Mar-Vell's Laboratory|battle]] and ordered the Accusers to drop the warheads onto the planet.
[[File:Ronan the Accuser (1995).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan witnesses [[Captain Marvel]]'s attack]]
However, once the Accusers dropped the warheads, Ronan was astonished to see them being destroyed by Captain Marvel. As she approached their ships, Ronan ordered for Captain Marvel to be taken down, but seeing how she easily dispatched the fleet and single-handedly destroyed a warship, Ronan admitted imminent defeat and decided to retreat. However, along with a fellow [[Accuser]], he vowed that they would soon return to get her back and use her as a weapon.{{Ref|CM}}

===Demobilization of the Accusers===
After failing to win the [[Kree-Skrull War]], Ronan eventually lost his high standing with the [[Kree Empire]] when the [[Accusers]] were demobilized. However, he continued going by his former title.{{Ref|CM}}{{Ref|GotG}}

===[[Kree-Nova War]]===
====Outrage over Peace====
{{Quote|Who's Ronan?"<br>"A [[Kree]] fanatic, outraged by the peace treaty, who will not rest until [[Xandarian]] culture, my culture, is wiped from existence!|[[Star-Lord]] and [[Broker]]|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
Years later, the [[Kree Empire]] and the [[Nova Empire]] had signed a peace treaty to end the [[Kree-Nova War|war]], which Ronan found disgusting and unacceptable. Desperate to annihilate [[Xandar]] and it people, Ronan defected from the [[Accusers]] and put together his own army, including [[Korath the Pursuer]] of the [[Starforce]], the [[Sakaarans]] and a sect of the [[Exolon Monks]]. The Kree Empire denounced Ronan and his agenda, branding him as a rogue terrorist, but failed to stop his conflict against the Nova Empire.{{Ref|GotG}}

===Thanos' Underling===
====Deal with the Mad Titan====
{{Quote|I promised [[Thanos]] I would retrieve the [[Orb]] for him. Only then will he destroy [[Xandar]] for me.|Ronan|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
Seeking the power that could help him achieve his goals, Ronan made an alliance with [[Thanos]], promising to work for him in exchange for his eventual help in the destruction of [[Xandar]]. Ronan was ordered by Thanos to lead an attack on a planet, which resulted in half of the native population being slaughtered. Ronan would personally kill [[Ovette]] and her daughter, [[Kamaria]], finding their dying screams to be "pitiful," which prompted [[Drax]] to vow revenge on him and Thanos.{{Ref|GotG}}

Ronan's most important mission was to find the [[Orb]], as Thanos made it clear that Xandar will be destroyed only after he brings the artifact to him. Ronan and his subordinates succeeded and discovered the Orb on [[Morag]], which he informed Thanos about. Thanos dispatched [[Gamora]] and [[Nebula]] to the ''[[Dark Aster]]'' to make sure Ronan succeeded in procuring the Orb, threatening him with death in case he refuseed.{{Ref|AE}} Ronan then sent [[Korath the Pursuer]] and a small unit of [[Sakaarans]] to Morag to retrieve it from the [[Temple Vault]].{{Ref|GotG}}

====Gamora's Betrayal====
[[File:Ronan-Armor.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan is dressed into his [[Kree Armor|battle armor]]]]
{{Quote|You can't do this. [[Kree Empire|Our]] [[Nova Empire|governments]] signed a peace treaty!"<br>"My government knows no shame. You [[Xandarians]] and your culture are a disease."<br>"You will never rule [[Xandar]]."<br>"No. I will cure it!|[[Sacrifice Nova Corpsman]] and Ronan|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
On the ''[[Dark Aster]]'', Ronan was awoken from his nap in [[Celestial]] blood{{Ref|GttMCUGotG}} and dressed in his armor by the [[Exolon Monks]] before he began a ritualistic killing of a captured member of the [[Nova Corps]]. When the [[Sacrifice Nova Corpsman|Corpsman]] insisted that he would never be able to rule [[Xandar]], Ronan told the Corpsman that he intended to cure Xandar before crushing his head with his [[Universal Weapon]]. As Ronan watched the Corpsman's blood draining away, [[Nebula]] informed him that [[Korath the Pursuer]] had returned from [[Morag]].
[[File:RonanLearnsOfStarLord.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan learns [[Star-Lord]] has stolen the [[Orb]]]]
Korath informed Ronan that the Orb had been taken from him by [[Star-Lord]]; Korath explained that his sources had learned that Star-Lord intended to sell the Orb to the [[Broker]] on [[Xandar]]. Ronan, unwilling to be denied his chance for vengeance and desire not to incur the furious wrath of [[Thanos]], made his decision and ordered Nebula to travel to Xandar and retrieve the Orb from Star-Lord, by any means necessary.
[[File:YouWillNotFail.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan orders [[Gamora]] to find the [[Orb]]]]
[[Gamora]], however, insisted that she should be the one to go as she knew Xandar and Nebula would likely get herself killed. Ronan agreed and sent Gamora to Xandar, telling her not to fail in her mission. Ronan, however, was unaware that Gamora had decided to leave her life as a killer and planned on betraying him and Thanos by selling the orb to a third party: the [[Collector]], using the money to escape from her family and her life of killing.
[[File:RonanAndNebula.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan and [[Nebula]] speak to [[Other]]]]
Soon, Ronan was informed that Gamora had been captured during her mission and incarcerated in the [[Kyln]]. When Thanos learned about Gamora's betrayal, he summoned Ronan and Nebula to the [[Sanctuary]] to discuss the recent events. Although Ronan still insisted that Gamora was likely simply captured and was still planning on delivering the Orb to them, [[Other]] informed him that Thanos had sources inside the Kyln who confirmed Gamora's betrayal and demanded that he could speak to him immediately in person.{{Ref|GotG}}

====Speaking to Thanos====
[[File:Ronan and the Other.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan stands before [[Thanos]]]]
{{Quote|I only ask that you take this matter seriously."<br>"The only matter I do not take seriously, boy, is you. Your [[Kree-Nova War|politics]] bore me. Your demeanor is that of a pouty child. And apparently, you alienated my favorite daughter, [[Gamora]]. I shall honor our agreement, [[Kree]], if you bring me the [[Orb]]. But return to me again empty handed... And I will bathe the starways in your blood.|Ronan and [[Thanos]]|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
Once they arrived at the [[Sanctuary]], [[Other]] spoke for [[Thanos]], accusing Ronan of being the cause of [[Gamora]]'s betrayal and demanded Ronan show [[Thanos]] respect. However, Ronan insisted that Thanos was to blame for everything that had gone wrong. When the Other's taunts began to annoy him, Ronan killed him by breaking his neck with his [[Universal Weapon]], demanding that Thanos face him and take the situation more seriously.
[[File:RonanAngry-GOTG.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan's life is threatened by [[Thanos]]]]
Thanos was unaffected by his servant's death; however, he mocked and threatened Ronan, claiming that his politics bored him and his entire demeanor was pathetic. Once Ronan was unable to speak out of fear, Thanos insisted that he would still honor their agreement to destroy [[Xandar]], but if he failed him again, then he would bathe the starways in his blood. [[Nebula]] then confirmed that Ronan would never win a war against Thanos.{{Ref|GotG}}

====Cleansing the Kyln====
[[File:Ronan-KylnPrison.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan learns that [[Gamora]] has escaped]]
{{Quote|Send [[Necrocraft]] to every corner of the quadrant. Find the [[Orb]]. Any means, any price."<br>"And [[Kyln|this place]]?"<br>"The [[Nova Corps|Nova]] can't know what we're after. Cleanse it!|Ronan and [[Nebula]]|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
[[Thanos]] ordered Ronan and [[Nebula]] to raid the [[Kyln]] in order to locate the missing [[Orb]] and capture [[Gamora]]. By the time they arrived with their army of [[Sakaarans]], Gamora had already escaped from the prison with their prize along with her new [[Guardians of the Galaxy|allies]] as she continued her quest to sell the Orb to the [[Collector]] and escape her life of violence and death that Ronan had forced upon her.
[[File:Ronan-CleansesKylnPrison.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan orders to kill everyone in [[Kyln]]]]
Furious that he was once again failing in his quest to locate the Orb for [[Thanos]], Ronan ordered Nebula to capture and torture the guards in an attempt to learn Gamora's location but found the [[List of Minor Characters/Phase Two#Guardians of the Galaxy|guard]] did not know. Realizing that the [[Nova Corps]] was coming to retake the prison and that none of the staff had any information, Ronan ordered Nebula and their Sakaaran soldiers to cleanse the prison and [[Massacre at the Kyln|have everybody inside executed]] to keep them silent.{{Ref|GotG}}

====[[Skirmish on Knowhere]]====
[[File:RonanGlaresAtDrax.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan is confronted by [[Drax the Destroyer]]]]
{{Quote|I don't recall killing your family. I doubt I'll remember killing you either.|Ronan to [[Drax]]|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
Ronan and his subordinates worked to track [[Gamora]] and her allies, while [[Nebula]] asked if Ronan ever wondered why [[Thanos]] wanted the [[Orb]], but Ronan simply said it was not his place. [[Drax the Destroyer]], who desired revenge for Ronan killing his [[Ovette|wife]] and [[Kamaria|daughter]], sent a transmission to Ronan, challenging him to go to [[Knowhere]] and face death. Nebula explained that Drax was the prisoner who escaped the [[Kyln]] along with Gamora and her associates, so Ronan concluded that the Orb was on Knowhere,{{Ref|AIWTHJ}} leading an attack on the planet. When Gamora attempted to flee, Ronan turned to pursue only to be confronted and attacked by the furious Drax and so had [[Nebula]] pursue her instead while he stayed behind.
[[File:RonanPinsDrax.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan subdues [[Drax the Destroyer]]]]
Drax launched numerous ferocious attacks upon Ronan, but Ronan was easily able to evade Drax's attacks, as his furious rage made him predictable and foolish. As Drax continued to attack his foe, Ronan overpowered him several times while landing several powerful strikes of his own and soon disarmed him of his [[Drax the Destroyer's Knives|knives]]. To prove a point, Ronan even allowed Drax to repeatedly punch him in the stomach to no effect, only watching while Drax's furious rage continued to grow.
[[File:Ronan-0.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan attempts to drown [[Drax]]]]
Eventually, Ronan beat Drax half to death and slammed his body onto the ground, claiming that he could not recall slaughtering his family and would unlikely ever remember killing him either. With Drax the so-called Destroyer defeated and unable to defend himself, Ronan left him to drown in a vat of spinal fluid. Nebula then called Ronan, having retrieved the Orb and, with this information, Ronan returned to the ''[[Dark Aster]]'' to claim his victory.{{Ref|GotG}}

===Betraying Thanos===
====Claiming the Power Stone====
[[File:RonanNebulaKorath-Thanos.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan updates [[Thanos]] on his success]]
{{Quote|Boy! I would reconsider your current course!"<br>"You call me boy?! I will unfurl one thousand years of [[Kree]] justice on [[Xandar]] and burn it to its core! Then, Thanos... I'm coming for you.|[[Thanos]] and Ronan|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
With the [[Orb]] now in his possession, Ronan returned to the ''[[Dark Aster]]'' and contacted [[Thanos]] to report his success. However, when Thanos demanded that Ronan bring him the Orb immediately, Ronan told him that he had reconsidered their deal now he was aware that the Orb contained [[Power Stone|one]] of the [[Infinity Stones]] and questioned his need for Thanos' assistance in his quest for revenge.
[[File:NoMasterKorathRonan.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan takes the [[Orb]]'s power for himself]]
[[Nebula]] handed the [[Orb]] over to Ronan who, ignoring the demands of Thanos and [[Korath the Pursuer]]'s fears, ripped it apart in order to reveal the powerful stone within. Unafraid of its power, Ronan ripped the [[Power Stone]] from the Orb and consumed its energy, causing explosions all around him before he embedded it in the [[Universal Weapon]] in order to control its force, becoming more powerful than even Thanos himself, who watched in silence at the betrayal.
[[File:Ronan-YouDareOpposeMe.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan is joined by [[Nebula]] in his quest]]
As a result, Ronan decided that he no longer needed Thanos' help in invading [[Xandar]] and so severed ties with the Titan. Ronan then roared at his former master that, for his insults and mockery, after he ensured that Xandar was destroyed in the name of the [[Kree Empire]], he would be coming to destroy him next. Nebula, having resented Thanos' treatment of her over the years, joined Ronan and vowed to help him destroy a thousand planets if he destroyed her monstrous adoptive father, starting with Xandar.{{Ref|GotG}}

====[[Battle of Xandar]]====
[[File:Ronan.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan begins his attack upon [[Xandar]]]]
{{Quote|[[Xandar]], you stand accused. Your wretched peace treaty will not save you now. 'Tis the tinder on which you burn!|Ronan|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
As they approached [[Xandar]] ready to begin the destruction of the planet, the ''[[Dark Aster]]'' was confronted by the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]] along with the [[Yondu Ravager Clan]], led by [[Yondu Udonta]]. Still confident in his power, Ronan remained calm and watched as the ''[[Eclector]]'' fired a wall of flame at the ship before attempting to breach the side, with [[Nebula]] sending out their own fleet of [[Necrocraft]] to battle them above the skies of Xandar while Ronan looked on, remaining confident even when the [[Nova Corps]] arrived to assist the Ravagers in the battle, forming a blockade around the ''Dark Aster'' to stop its movement.
[[File:RonanNebula-NovaCorpsAttack.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan learns of the [[Nova Corps]]' attack]]
Ronan ordered that the ''Dark Aster'' continue pushing forward while his [[Sakaarans]] battle the attacks in the sky and when the battleship was boarded by the Guardians after [[Kraglin Obfonteri]] had breached the side of the ship, Ronan sent [[Nebula]] to kill them as he believed their only focus should be to reach the planet's surface so he could destroy it. The Nova Corps stalled the ship's approach on Xandar while [[Rocket]] and the Ravagers protected the civilians.
[[File:Ronan-YouBurn.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan destroys the [[Nova Corps]]' entire army]]
Unfazed by his enemies' attack and filled with more power than all of them combined, Ronan responded by standing before the fleet of Nova Corps ships and accusing them before sentencing them to destruction. Ronan then used the Stone's power to fire a powerful blast from the [[Universal Weapon]] which destroyed the Nova Corps' entire fleet, as the burning remains of the army flew to the ground below and Ronan looked at the destruction with a sense of satisfaction as he saw the pain he was causing to his enemies.
[[File:Ronan the Accuser.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan attacks the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]]]]
While continuing to watch the battle unfold, Ronan found himself confronted by [[Star-Lord]], [[Gamora]], [[Drax the Destroyer]], and [[Groot (Original)|Groot]] after they had defeated Nebula and [[Korath the Pursuer]] during their hunt for him. The Guardians subdued his bodyguards and shot Ronan in the chest with the [[Hadron Enforcer]], causing a small explosion. However, Ronan was barely affected by the blast and was merely knocked off his feet. Ronan then easily overpowered the group with a single shockwave blast from his hammer.
[[File:Ronan-strangles-Drax-Dark-Aster.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan strangles [[Drax the Destroyer]]]]
Drax the Destroyer attempted to fight Ronan once again on his own, but Ronan simply grabbed his throat and began to choke him as he lifted him off the ground while mocking him about his dead family, claiming that he recalled their screams which he viewed as pitiful. However, before Ronan could finally destroy the team, [[Rocket]] crashed his [[Warbird|ship]] into the ''Dark Aster'', knocking over Ronan, heavily damaging the ship, and sending it plummeting to the ground.{{Ref|GotG}}

====Interrupted Vengeance====
[[File:Ronandustintheair.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan steps onto the surface of [[Xandar]]]]
{{Quote|Behold! Your [[Guardians of the Galaxy]]! What fruit have they wrought? Only that my father and his father shall finally know vengeance. People of [[Xandar]], the time has come to rejoice and renounce your paltry gods! Your salvation is at hand.|Ronan|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
The ''[[Dark Aster]]'' crashed to the surface of [[Xandar]], as [[Groot (Original)|Groot]] sacrificed his life to save his teammates from the explosion. However, Ronan was unharmed as he walked calmly out of his ship's wreckage, to the horror of the citizens looking on. [[Rocket]] furiously attempted to attack him in revenge for killing his dear friend Groot, but Ronan easily used an energy blast to shoot him away.
[[File:RonansHammerPowerStone-GOTG.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan is distracted by [[Star-Lord|Star-Lord's]] dancing]]
Smiling to himself at the desperate and pathetic attempts to stop him that had been proved to be worthless, Ronan mocked the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]] and prepared to unleash the [[Power Stone|Stone]]'s power to annihilate Xandar. However, before he could unleash the stone's power, he became distracted by [[Star-Lord]], who had challenged him to a dance-off. Genuinely confused by this turn of events, the distraction allowed Rocket enough time to repair the [[Hadron Enforcer]] allowing [[Drax the Destroyer]] to fire it at him, destroying Ronan's [[Universal Weapon]], disarming him and leaving the [[Power Stone]] hovering in the air before him.
[[File:RonanVsPeter.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan attempts to catch the [[Power Stone]]]]
In a desperate move to gain the advantage in the battle and kill each other, both Ronan and Quill attempted to catch the Stone during the split second it hung unprotected in the air before them. Despite Ronan's best efforts to regain the powerful weapon and complete his plan, however, Quill was a moment faster and quickly caught the Stone while [[Gamora]] called out in horror, as she was aware of what the Stone's power would do to a mortal human like Quill.{{Ref|GotG}}

====Destroyed by the Power Stone====
[[File:Ronan-PurpleLightShow.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan watches as [[Star-Lord]] is nearly killed]]
{{Quote|You're mortal! How?!..."<br>"You said it yourself, bitch. We're the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]].|Ronan and [[Star-Lord]]|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
The moment the [[Power Stone]] was touched by [[Peter Quill]]'s hand, it unleashed a massive amount of energy, causing a shock-wave which threw Ronan backwards as flames engulfed their group. As Ronan watched on with a sense of delight, the Stone's incredible and near uncontrollable power almost killed Quill as his body was slowly ripped apart from the inside by the Power Stone. Ronan then laughed as he watched Quill screaming in horrific pain, believing that once Quill was dead, he could then reclaim the Power Stone.
[[File:Ronan's Death.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ronan is destroyed by the [[Power Stone]]]]
However, Ronan witnessed [[Gamora]], [[Drax the Destroyer]], and [[Rocket]] join hands as a team and grab Quill's hand, helping with the burden of the Stone's power and gaining complete control over it. Ronan looked on in horror and demanded to know how that was possible for a human to survive such power, and Quill informed him it was because together they were a team, they were able to control it. Ronan furiously attempted to attack them with his ruined [[Universal Weapon]]'s handle, but they directed the Stone's energy at Ronan, painfully destroying his body and killing him for good.{{Ref|GotG}}

===Legacy===
====Impact on the Galaxy====
{{Quote|The [[Kree]] purists, the [[Ravagers]], they all want us dead.|[[Star-Lord]] to [[Gamora]]|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2}}
News of Ronan's demise quickly reached [[Hala]] and incurred great outrage amongst the "purist" denizens of the [[Kree Empire]], who marked the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]] as heretics and enemies of the [[Kree]] people.{{Ref|GotGV2}} When [[Ego]] heard the news of the [[Battle of Xandar]], planning to recruit his son to aid him on his [[Ego's Expansion|plot]] to assimilate the universe, he built a memorial statue of the Guardians with a defeated Ronan at Quill's feet, even though [[Gamora]] noted that the statue did not show how the battle actually happened.{{Ref|GotGV2DS}} Ronan's death at the hands of the Guardians of the Galaxy was one of the many factors that contributed to [[Thanos]]' plan to [[Infinity War|obtain]] the [[Infinity Stones]].

[[2018|Four years]] after his death, Thanos ironically fulfilled Ronan's desire to completely destroy the [[Nova Empire]] when he [[Massacre of the Xandarians|invaded]] [[Xandar]], killing all of the [[Nova Corps]] and slaughtering half the population in the process before retrieving the [[Orb]].{{Ref|AIW}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved by Wiki-Projects with the media released as of the end of 2021. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. -->
*'''Kree Physiology''': As a [[Kree]], Ronan possessed all of the natural attributes common among his people, such as blue skin coloration as well as superhuman strength, durability, and recuperation. However, it appears that his natural attributes are greater than most of his species, likely due to his status as an Accuser and his advanced technology.
**'''Superhuman Strength''': [[File:Ronaaaaan-1-.jpg|thumb|250px|Ronan effortlessly lifting up [[Drax]]]] Ronan was known to be among the strongest of the Krees, even being worshipped by some for his great power. Ronan possessed enough strength to easily overpower someone as strong as [[Drax the Destroyer]], even tossing him around like a rag doll and heavily staggering him. His strength was even impressive enough to allow him to survive direct exposure to the [[Power Stone]]'s power long enough until combining it with his Universal Weapon. His exposure to the [[Infinity Stones|Infinity Stone]] appeared to have greatly augmented his physical strength, as he easily defeated the Guardians of the Galaxy.
**'''Superhuman Durability''': [[File:RonanGlowingStone.PNG|thumb|250px|Ronan withstands [[Power Stone]]'s energy]] While not indestructible, Ronan had incredible durability that was well beyond that of a [[human]]. He was unfazed by Drax's best punches and temporarily endured the intense energy of the [[Power Stone]]. After being augmented by its power, he was even able to withstand an attack from the [[Hadron Enforcer]], a weapon said by [[Rocket]] to be powerful enough to destroy entire moons.
**'''Superhuman Agility''': Ronan's agility was outmatched by the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]]. Despite usually watching the battle from his ship, he was always ready to make a move when getting attacked.
**'''Superhuman Stamina''': Ronan fought the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]] for a long period of time and did not have any fatigue while the Guardians laid on the ground, struggling to get up.
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': Ronan had a very fast reaction time despite his size. He effortlessly evaded [[Drax the Destroyer]]'s attacks when he charged against him inside [[Knowhere]].
**'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': As with all Kree, Ronan possessed a healing factor which allowed him to recover from injuries in a much shorter time span than [[Humans]]. His hand healed very quickly after it was scarred by the [[Power Stone]] when he briefly held it in his hand.
**'''Longevity''': Ronan and his [[Kree|race]] can live for a very long time. This allowed Ronan to rise through the ranks of the [[Accusers]] in the span of around twenty years.
{{Quote|Master! You cannot! [[Thanos]] is the most powerful being in the universe."<br>"Not anymore.|[[Korath the Pursuer]] and Ronan|Guardians of the Galaxy (film)}}
*'''[[Universal Weapon]] Capabilities''': Ronan's trusted weapon was the [[Universal Weapon]], which was a hammer that he carried around with him everywhere. He also infused the [[Power Stone]] into the hammer making it more powerful.
**'''Concussive Blast''': Using the [[Universal Weapon]], Ronan could point it at his enemy and twist the hammer which set off a concussive blast that defeated his opponents. He used this technique to easily knock the [[Guardians of the Galaxy|Guardians]] off their feet.

===Abilities===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved by Wiki-Projects with the media released as of the end of 2021. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. -->
*'''Master Combatant''': [[File:Drax-vs-Ronan-GotG.jpg|thumb|250px|Ronan fighting against [[Drax the Destroyer]]]] As a warrior and military figurehead, it is only natural that Ronan would have extensive combat and military training. He had a very impressive hand to hand skills, easily countering [[Drax the Destroyer]]'s hits and defeating him in battle with little effort as well as later overpowering the Guardians of the Galaxy while enhanced by the [[Power Stone]] easily.
*'''Hammer Mastery''': Thanks to his training, Ronan is extremely proficient in wielding melee weapons, especially his hammer, the [[Universal Weapon]]. He infused this hammer with the [[Power Stone]] to make it even more powerful and he carried it around with him everywhere.
*'''Expert Tactician''': Ronan was an experienced and exonerated member of the [[Kree]] military, and as such, he was a highly trained strategist. He led the [[Sakaarans]] during the [[Battle of Xandar]]. Ronan also led his forces above [[Torfa]] and [[Earth|C-53]].

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''[[Universal Weapon]]''': [[File:RonanUniversalWeapon-GOTG.png|thumb|250px|Ronan uses the [[Universal Weapon]] for annihilation]] Ronan was the wielder of the powerful hammer known as the [[Universal Weapon]], a large staff-like war hammer. In addition to using it as a melee weapon, he can also fire some sort of force that is capable of snapping a person's neck by twisting their head 180 degrees, as he did to [[Other]]. When Ronan pushed the [[Power Stone]] into the Weapon, the hammer increased in power and became capable of firing blasts of energy which annihilated the entire [[Nova Corps]] fleet and came close to being used to destroy [[Xandar]].
*'''[[Orb]]''': Ronan came into possession of the Orb and embedded the Power Stone within it in his Universal Weapon to try and destroy [[Xandar]], instead of bringing it to [[Thanos]] as Ronan promised.

===Other Equipment===
*'''[[Kree Armor]]''': Ronan used a technologically advanced battle-suit that enhanced his strength and durability to levels higher than they already were. The Armor was powerful enough not to shatter when shot in the chest plate with the [[Hadron Enforcer]], although Ronan's strength had been considerably increased by this stage.

===Vehicles===
*'''[[Accuser Warship]]''': As a member of the [[Accusers]], Ronan had his personal warship while he was in command of the Accusers' fleet that was used during the [[Kree-Skrull War]]. Ronan led the fleet aboard his own ship to eliminate the [[Skrulls]] on [[Torfa]] and attempted to attack the [[Earth]], however, the fleet was seriously damaged by [[Captain Marvel]], forcing Ronan to order the remaining Accusers to retreat.
**'''''[[Dark Aster]]''''': When he defected from the [[Kree Empire]], Ronan was the commander of a warship, codenamed the ''Dark Aster'', which came with armies of [[Sakaarans]] who acted as Ronan's complete crew and combat squadron.
*'''[[Necrocraft]]''': Upon getting word of the [[Orb]]'s location from [[Drax the Destroyer]], Ronan and his army flew to [[Knowhere]] on board a Necrocraft to investigate.

