==Trivia==
*In the comics, Ronan was an anti-hero and was torn between his loyalties to the [[Kree]] and the [[Earth]] defenders with whom he allied on several occasions: he even became the second husband of [[Crystal]] and a member of the Annihilators.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Lee Pace]] originally auditioned for the role of [[Star-Lord]] after reading the script in 2012, but he ended up cast as Ronan whereas [[Chris Pratt]] was cast as Star-Lord.<ref>[https://www.slashfilm.com/lee-pace-confirms-hes-auditioning-for-guardians-of-the-galaxy-says-script-is-great/ Lee Pace Confirms He’s Auditioning For ‘Guardians of the Galaxy;’ Says Script Is ‘Great’]</ref>
*[[Lee Pace]] noted that Ronan is a "''f*cking psycho''" and "''a monster''".<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20170731182709/https://clickonline.com/movies/lee-pace-on-his-guardians-of-the-galaxy-character--hes-a-fcking-psycho!/20579/ Lee Pace on His Guardians of the Galaxy Character - 'He's a f**king psycho!']</ref>
*Early concept art for ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy (film)|Guardians of the Galaxy]]'' by [[Marvel Studios]]' Director of Visual Development and concept artist [[Andy Park]] had a more intimidating and armored Ronan in mind before his final design was decided.<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/p/BmoFWxXAJa7/?utm_source=ig_embed This is an early Ronan concept design version I did on the 1st Guardians of the Galaxy film. That was a special time fairly early in the MCU. It was such an unknown property. I love that Ronan will be back in the new Captain Marvel film next year.]</ref>
*In retrospect, [[James Gunn]] regrets a little how Ronan was depicted in ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy (film)|Guardians of the Galaxy]]'': "''There is some messy villain plot stuff in the first movie I'd like to deal with again. There was a committee working for Marvel at the time (now defunct) who had a lot of input, and that was primarily where it ended up''".<ref>[https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a834953/guardians-of-the-galaxy-villain-problem-james-gunn-explains-ronan-the-accuser/ James Gunn explains why Guardians of the Galaxy's villain was so rubbish]</ref>
*Although [[Lee Pace]] expressed his interest in making a comeback as Ronan in ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'', [[James Gunn]] affirmed in a {{WPS|Facebook}} Q&A that he would not be appearing in that film, yet he did not discard any future appearances of Ronan in further installments of the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]].<ref>[https://wegotthiscovered.com/movies/james-gunn-ronan-accuser-return-guardians-of-the-galaxy-2/ James Gunn Says Ronan The Accuser Won’t Return For Guardians Of The Galaxy 2]</ref>
*Regarding Ronan's appearance in ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]'', directors [[Ryan Fleck]] and [[Anna Boden]] explained that they had a talk about introducing him earlier in the film or hold onto his introduction later, ultimately choosing the latter option because they felt that due to Ronan's antagonistic role in ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy (film)|Guardians of the Galaxy]]'', it was more effective for him to not be introduced earlier as it could have given away too soon that the Kree race was the villain and not the [[Skrulls]].{{Ref|CMAC}}
*Ronan was initially meant to have a bigger role in ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]''. Several [[List of Deleted Scenes|deleted scenes]] featuring Ronan, including one in which he interacted with the [[Starforce]] team face-to-face, have been leaked on {{WPS|Reddit}}.<ref>[https://comicbook.com/marvel/2019/03/10/captain-marvel-movie-2019-deleted-scenes-ronan-jude-law-yon-rogg/ 'Captain Marvel' Cut Scenes Revealed]</ref>
*Concept art for ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]'' shows that Ronan was planned to be featured with black markings on his face much like in ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy (film)|Guardians of the Galaxy]]''.<ref>[https://www.comicbookmovie.com/captain_marvel/captain-marvel-check-out-these-amazing-alternate-designs-for-ronan-the-accuser-and-korath-a167166 CAPTAIN MARVEL: Check Out These Amazing Alternate Designs For Ronan The Accuser And Korath]</ref>
*Ronan is the first main antagonist to be killed by the titular character(s) of the film in which he appears.

